<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1338,1684]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1338,1364]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from all other genera of Plesiolebiasini by the following unique features: posterior process of quadrate and sympletic long (
<emphasis box="[644,675,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vs.</emphasis>
short) (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[772,934,1378,1404]" pageId="19" pageNumber="41" refString="Costa, W. J. E. M. (1998 a) Phylogeny and classification of Rivulidae revisited: evolution of annualism and miniaturization in rivulid fishes (Cyprinodontiformes: Aplocheiloidei). Journal of Comparative Biology, 3, 33 - 92." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">
Costa, 
<number box="[859,921,1378,1404]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1998.0">1998</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), interarcual cartilage absent (
<emphasis box="[1300,1331,1379,1404]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vs.</emphasis>
present) (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[159,319,1418,1444]" pageId="19" pageNumber="41" refString="Costa, W. J. E. M. (1998 a) Phylogeny and classification of Rivulidae revisited: evolution of annualism and miniaturization in rivulid fishes (Cyprinodontiformes: Aplocheiloidei). Journal of Comparative Biology, 3, 33 - 92." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">
Costa, 
<number box="[243,305,1418,1444]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1998.0">1998</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), rays of anterior portion of anal fin longer than posterior rays (
<emphasis box="[1072,1104,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vs.</emphasis>
longer) (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[1213,1372,1418,1444]" pageId="19" pageNumber="41" refString="Costa, W. J. E. M. (1995 a) Two new genera and two new species of the neotropical annual fishes Plesiolebiasini (Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae), with studies on the relationships of the tribe. Revue Francaise d'Aquariologie, 21, 65 - 74." type="journal article" year="1995" yearSuffix="a">
Costa, 
<number box="[1297,1359,1418,1444]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1995.0">1995</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), and frontal squamation G-patterned (
<emphasis box="[536,567,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vs.</emphasis>
F or D patterned) (
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[793,952,1458,1484]" pageId="19" pageNumber="41" refString="Costa, W. J. E. M. (1998 a) Phylogeny and classification of Rivulidae revisited: evolution of annualism and miniaturization in rivulid fishes (Cyprinodontiformes: Aplocheiloidei). Journal of Comparative Biology, 3, 33 - 92." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">
Costa, 
<number box="[876,938,1458,1484]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1998.0">1998</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1338,1684]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,359,1498,1524]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Distribution.</emphasis>
Southeastern Amazonian basin, including Xingu, Araguaia, and Tocantins river drainages, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,226,1538,1564]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; and rio 
<collectingCountry box="[327,436,1538,1564]" name="Paraguay" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
basin, in northern Brazilian Pantanal (
<figureCitation box="[889,975,1538,1564]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,255,900,924]" captionTargetBox="[486,1100,184,883]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[486,1100,184,883]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Geographic distribution of genus Plesiolebias. Triangle = P. aruana; inverted triangle = P. altamira; star = P. filamentosus; dots = P. aruana and P. fragilis; square = P. canabravensis; six-tip asterisk = P. lacerdai; eight-tip asterisk = P. glaucopterus; lozenge = P. xavantei. One symbol may represent more than one collecting site." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175578/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 
<number box="[943,975,1538,1564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1338,1684]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,1578,1604]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
The systematic accounts below should be viewed as a complement to the recent taxonomic revision of 
<taxonomicName box="[291,434,1619,1644]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Plesiolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[291,434,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Plesiolebias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Costa" box="[453,614,1618,1644]" pageId="19" pageNumber="41" refString="Costa, W. J. E. M. (1998 c) Revision of the neotropical annual fish genus Plesiolebias (Cyprinodontiformes: Rivulidae). Ichthyological Exploration of Freshwaters, 8, 313 - 334." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="c">
Costa, 
<number box="[539,601,1618,1644]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1998.0">1998</number>
c
</bibRefCitation>
), where redescriptions of 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1062,1619,1644]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xavantei">
<emphasis box="[931,1062,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. xavantei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1080,1206,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. l a c e rd a i</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1227,1343,1619,1644]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Plesiolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aruana">
<emphasis box="[1227,1343,1619,1644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. aruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Plesiolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="glaucopterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. glaucopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are included.
</paragraph>
